5. Which is more secure? Which is least secure? Why?
WPA2, it is the newest. WEP, it is the oldest
6. What is AirSnort? What is it for? How does it work?
AirSnort is a Linux and Microsoft Windows utility (using GTK+) for decrypting WEP encryption on an 802.11b network. 
7. What is Kismet (for wireless)? What are its legal, legitimate uses?
Kismet is a wireless network detector, sniffer, and intrusion detection system. Kismet works predominately with Wi-Fi (IEEE 802.11) networks, but can be expanded via plug-ins to handle other network types. 
8. What is Karma (the wireless tool)?
It is a wireless devices that finds wifi connections and connects to them.
